CommonFields.Title: Carbon nanotube composites with high dielectric constant at low percolation threshold
Author: Wang, Lan
Dang, Zhi-Min
CommonFields.Location: Key Laboratory of Beijing City for Preparation and Processing of Novel Polymer Materials and Key Laboratory of the Ministry of Education on Nanomaterials, Beijing University of Chemical Technology, Beijing 100029, People's Republic of China

Mixing.Description: MWNT was ultrasonically dispersed in an organic solvent {N, N-dimethylformamide (DMF)] for as long as 2 h
At the same time, PVDF powder was disolved in the DMF solvent at 50 deg C
Then the suspension of MWNT in solvent was added into the PVDF solution, and the solution was stirred by further ultrasonic treatment for 10 min.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Afterwards, the solution was heated to 60 deg C for 8 h to completely evaporate the solvent.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: The fractured crossections of the samples were examined by transmission electron microscopy (TEM, Hitachi H-800)

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: Alternating current (ac) electric properties of the samples were measured using HP 4194A impedance in the frequency ranges of 100 Hz - 40 MHz at room temperature.

data.description: dielectric constant on frequency (Hz)  at room temperature for PVDF with 0.020 vol frac MWNT
conductivity (S/m) on frequency (Hz) at room temperature for PVDF with 0.020 vol frac MWNT
